<HEADLINE>
MORTON SAYS PREDICTION WAS MEANT TO FIRE UP TROJANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC tailback Chad Morton said he doesn't mind that
UCLA coach Bob Toledo is using him as motivational fodder, after
Morton predicted last summer that the Trojans would finally end
their losing streak against the Bruins at eight games.
</P>
<P>
   ``They probably have my face on a dartboard,'' Morton said.
``That's just part of football and college excitement. It's all
just fun.''
</P>
<P>
   Morton said his prediction was important for his teammates to
hear, even if it offended UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's going to be a big difference to our team to hear
`We're going to do it' instead of `We hope we do it,' '' Morton
said. ``It puts a little pressure on us and that's what we need.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Professor Fox: Two weeks ago, quarterback John Fox started
working as a student-teacher at Edison Elementary school in
Glendale, but it wasn't until this week that his first-graders
finally realized who he was.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were really surprised,'' Fox said. ``One of the kids came
up and said, `You didn't tell us you played soccer.' ''
</P>
<P>
   __ Simmons doubtful: Hackett said cornerback Antuan Simmons will
probably miss the game after back spasms forced him to spend
Tuesday and Wednesday nights at USC University Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   ``His back is hurting him,'' Hackett said. ``Antuan Simmons is
out of the game.''
</P>
<P>
   But later, Hackett said, ``I'm kind of hoping he can play. He's
very doubtful.''
</P>
<P>
   Simmons played 72 plays against Washington State, despite
hurting his back early last week.
</P>
<P>
   Without Simmons, 5-foot-8 freshman Darrell Rideaux would start.
After the Washington State game, Hackett joked about Rideaux's
pass-interference penalty that allowed the Cougars to have an extra
play after time expired.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a guy who was 3-feet tall on a guy who was 8-feet
tall,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   So what would he think of Rideaux matching up against 6-4 Danny
Farmer of UCLA? ``We'll have to stack two guys on top of each
other,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Lewis commits: Linebacker Traison Lewis of Rancho Cucamonga
High has orally committed to USC. Lewis (6-2, 231 pounds) was also
considering Washington and Wisconsin.
</P>
<P>
   He is rated as one of PrepStar magazine's Top 30 players in the
West. Lewis is the 10th player to commit to USC.
</P>
<P>
   __ Soward will rest: Wide receiver R. Jay Soward did not
practice Wednesday and will sit out today's practice to rest his
strained hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have any idea (how much he'll play),'' Hackett said.
``He had a little setback Tuesday. Let's shut him down and wait
until Saturday. I expect him to make some big plays.''
</P>
<P>
   Tight end Antoine Harris, who also has a strained hamstring, is
expected to start.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
