</P>
<P>
   &UR; CIRCUITS (Moved in ``a'' category) &QL; 
 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SHOPPING-BOTS (Undated) _ Customers need to be wary of
comparison shopping services on the web, called shopping bots.
Merchants pay for listings, not all merchants are included and
hardly any comparison services list the lowest price first
automatically. Sorting by price is an option customers have to
choose. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SHOPPING-ONLINE (Undated) _ An attempt to do all holiday
shopping on line by the online shopping columnist. She finds better
prices, no serendipitous purchases of glittery ornaments, and,
surprise, surprise _ crowds, just as bad as at the mall. By
Michelle Slatalla.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ The weekly computer column: a
basic guide to buying a computer. By Peter H. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-GEEK-NOTES (Undated) _ Techno news and notes: storing
medical records on line; the Old Faithful webcam; Bible wins
