   TRUCKS-BUYING (Undated) _ Buying an SUV or truck is just like
buying any other vehicle. You've done it before, but let's just do
it by the numbers this time as a countdown to happiness. By Bill
Griffith. 1030 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-INDUSTRY (Undated) _ The SUV and truck industry is about
people and vehicles. Folks buy trucks and SUVs to take skiing, haul
boats, lug kids and pets. By Bill Griffith. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-MODELS (Undated) _ It isn't just a truck anymore, or
words to that effect, was the prominent theme in GMC advertising
not long ago. But now trucks are hot, and GMC is putting the
emphasis on building trucks. By Jerry Morris. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-SUV (Undated) _ Just when you thought there could be
nothing new in sport utility vehicles, along comes BMW with an SUV
that performs like a BMW. By Jerry Morris. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-MINIVANS (Undated) _ Last year, Honda reaped accolades
with its Odyssey minivan. This year, Mazda's all-new MPV is also
headed for the winner's circle. By Jerry Morris. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-SPEED (Undated) -- The Ford Lightning is an F150 4 x 2
with a 5.4-liter Triton Supercharged Intercooled V-8. As its name
is intendeded to suggest, it's fast. By Jerry Morris. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-ISLAND (Ilseboro, Maine) _ An island auto show clearly
reveals what a big part trucks (and now SUVs) have played in island
life over the years. By Bill Griffith. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-SUBURBAN (Undated) _ In 1978, the Silverado Suburban
seemed like the perfect answer. Besides, who had heard of the SUV?
By Bill Griffith. 830 words.
</P>
