<P>
   SLAVERY-COMMENTARY _ A significant number of Southerners deny
that slavery had much to do with Southern secession. They point to
states' rights, self-determination, liberty, protection of hearth
and home, everything but slavery. No historical event as vast as
the creation of a Southern nation can be explained in monocausal
terms. But there can be no doubt about the centrality of racial
slavery to the creation of the Confederacy. In fact, no slavery, no
Confederacy. (Roark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _Letters, I get letters ... A recent column
on snakes brought a variety of responses. (Ernest Murray is
managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ Just think. We have only 11 1/2 months until
the next presidential election. I can hardly wait. It seems as if
the candidates have been running since the Berlin Wall fell _ and a
few have, such as Al Gore and Steve Forbes. (Gary Borders is editor
and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel.) MOVED. EMBARGOED
for Sunday.
</P>
