<P>
   TORREYEA-PARK (36 inches) _ Torreyea State Park is one of the
best views in Florida, simple, solitary, splendid. The eye wings up
over tranquil miles of tufted forests, fading from green to blue in
the distance, to a horizon of rain-washed pure air. Hundreds of
feet below, beyond a steep tumble of trees and shrubs, the
toffee-colored Apalachicola River runs
</P>
<P>
   calmly to the Gulf of Mexico. Celebrate Florida's state park
system's being named the best in the nation by the National
Recreation and Parks Administration and the National Sporting Goods
Association at an Oct. 23 ceremony in Nashville. Florida beat
Missouri, ennessee and Virginia for the gold medal. By Michael
Browning
