   WITH: VIDEO REVIEWS _ As shaggy as it is shagadelic, ``Austin
Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me'' is really just an excuse to revel
in gleeful bad taste. Also reviews of ``Tea with Mussolini,'' ``The
Loss of Sexual Innocence,'' and ``Instinct.'' (Staff, Cox News
Service) Art includes an 18-pica color photo from ``Austin Powers:
The Spy Who Shagged Me.''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CD REVIEWS _ It might be misleading to call ``The Battle
of Los Angeles'' the best rock album of the year. In so many ways,
Rage Against the Machine's third effort sounds like the only rock
album of the year. Also reviews of the latest from the Pet Shop
Boys and Fiona Apple. (Staff, Cox News Service) art includes a
6-pica color photo of Fiona Apple.
</P>
<P>
   With: COMMENTARY _ In television interviews, enlightenment, not
embarrassment, should be the motivation. When the motivation is
embarrassment, the result is ``gotcha journalism.'' (Holloway,
Austin American-Statesman)
