Princess Mononoke and discusses the state of japanese animation.
(Larsen, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-HOLIDAY _ The end-of-the-year holiday movies and major
Oscar contenders kick in this week with ``Toy Story 2'' and ``End
of Days.'' We take an early peek at some of the major films coming
_ including Tom Hanks' prison drama ``The Green Mile,'' ``Angela's
Ashes'' (based on the popular book), Ang Lee's ``Ride With The
Devil'' (twentysomethings fighting the Civil War), the art-house
contender ``Topsy-Turvy'' (a lush, expertly costumed look at the
team of Gilbert and Sullivan), ``Cider House Rules'' and, of
course, ``Toy Story 2.'' Plus we detail the latest buzz on other
coming films, including Denzel Washington's ``The Hurricane,'' Matt
Damon's ``The Talented Mr. Ripley,'' Jodie Foster's ``Anna and the
King'' and Jim Carrey's ``Man on the Moon'' (featuring music from
R.E.M.). (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
