   CASPIAN-OIL (Istanbul) _ In a policy victory for the Clinton
administration, Turkey, Azerbaijan and Georgia signed a deal to
build a pipeline that would send the oil riches of the Caspian Sea
to international markets without going through Russia or Iran. By
Stephen Kinzer.
