<P>
   SPORTS-PARENTS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The Jupiter-Tequesta
Athletic Association has a novel idea for the 6,000 kids in its
youth leagues. Make good sportsmanship mandatory _ for the parents.
Beginning Jan. 1, the JTAA will be the first youth group in the
nation to require parents to attend an ethics class. (O'Meilia,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
