<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STATES-BUDGET </SLUG>
  THIS IS THE STATES NEWS SERVICE BUDGET FOR NOV.
18, 1999. IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS, PLEASE CALL US AT
202-628-3100.
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALIFORNIA-DVC. Diablo Valley College will receive $500,000 to
recruit and train teachers under a bill expected to be approved
today by the House of Representatives. (300 words). By Mark
Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   GEORGIA-BUDGET-REACT. Reaction from Reps. Charlie Norwood,
R-Ga., and Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., on today's spending bill vote
which should wrap up the congressional session until next year. (12
inches) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
<P>
   MICHIGAN-ROSA. The Rosa and Raymond Parks Institute for Self
Development will receive $1 million in federal funding as part of
the multi-billion spending package approved by Congress today. (300
words) By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   MULTICHANNEL-JOHNSON. Black Entertainment Television CEO Bob
Johnson told a lunch audience of telecommunications lawyers that
government policies are still closing the doors on minority
opportunities in the industry. (450 words) By Barney McManigal
</P>
<P>
   NEW MEXICO-MONEY. An analysis of where campaign contributions
from the city of Santa Fe are going. (700 words) By Jonathan Lipman
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-WAGE. One dollar may not seem like a lot of money, but to
congressional lawmakers and local officials, an hourly dollar
increase in the minimum wage which recently passed the U.S. Senate
means different things. (600 words) By Sean Gorman
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-ACCIDENT-A&AMP;M. The log pile accident at Texas A&AMP;M
University in College Station today shocked Texas lawmakers, who
made phone calls -- and in one case a plane flight - to express
their concern for families of the dead or injured. (300 words) By
Alex Canizares
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-BUDGET-DAIRY. A very chagrinned Wisconsin
congressional delegation stood together today to vote against a
final spending bill that includes provisions that would override
the long-awaited proposed USDA reforms that would have revamped the
milk pricing system. (15 inches) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
