   BOOKS-HILLARY _ Maybe it's her we should be building a library
for, not her husband. It probably goes without saying that Hillary
Rodham Clinton has broken the mold when it comes to U.S. first
ladies. It's still about 18 months until her husband leaves office,
and yet some 40 books already have been written largely or
completely about her. (Even the relatively controversial Nancy
Reagan barely hit double figures _ well after leaving the White
House.) And apparently, the deluge is just beginning. Last month it
was ``Bill and Hillary _ The Marriage.'' Come November it will be
publication of dueling tomes (including one from ``Passages''
author Gail Sheehy) purporting to take us inside Hillary's head.
And don't even get us started on the writers who've already signed
contracts to produce books about the all-but-declared Hillary
Clinton-Rudy Giuliani Senate race. A look at the phenomenon of
Hillary Literature and speculation on when _ and if _ it will ever
end. (Vejnoska, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
