<SLUG> BC-STUDENTSCRUSHED-REPORTER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REPORTER FACES STUDENTS' ANGER AT ACCIDENT SITE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LESLIE STEBBINS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLLEGE STATION, Texas _ As the tragedy unfolded at Texas A&AMP;M
University on Thursday, Sallie Turner of Fort Worth was in the
heart of it.
</P>
<P>
   Turner is the editor of ``The Battalion,'' the daily student
newspaper. A 1996 graduate of Arlington Heights High School in Fort
Worth, Turner is a senior journalism major.
</P>
<P>
   She had left the newspaper office around 1 a.m. Thursday after
completing work on the daily edition. She had less than two hours
to relax before a staff member phoned to tell her that a stack of
bonfire logs had collapsed with dozens of Aggies on top.
</P>
<P>
   Turner rushed to the site and began taking pictures, and said
she was attacked by students who had gathered to pray for the dead
and injured.
</P>
<P>
   ``I began taking pictures of the group when they started to
attack me,'' Turner said. ``They tore the lens cap off my camera
and hit me.''
</P>
<P>
   Throughout the day, Turner interrupted her reporting to give
interviews to various TV stations and networks, explaining the
Aggie bonfire tradition.
</P>
<P>
   Turner promised that the student newspaper will use the utmost
respect in covering the story.
</P>
<P>
   The paper had gone to press before the accident, but the front
page was pulled and a special edition was printed to inform the
43,000 students what had happened.
</P>
<P>
   Turner said she had been to the bonfire site Wednesday night to
admire the work of students who toiled around the clock to assemble
the structure. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I was dropping a friend off at their car when I thought about
how I wished I could be out there helping,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Leslie Stebbins of Burleson, Texas, is a junior at Texas A&AMP;M
University.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
