<HEADLINE>
BOUNTIFUL HARVEST FROM THE SLOP OF THE SEA
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Way to wash,  &UR; Marcia Settle  &LR; and  &UR; David Gilson &LR; , who thought it
was just a bar of soap they were buying at the New York branch of
the French scent store L'Occitane. After they'd left the store,
they glanced at the bag in which it had been handed to them and
realized the purchase had global environmental import. According to
a statement on the bag:
</P>
<P>
   ``Printed on paper manufactured using seaweed, harvested from
cleaning the Venice lagoon. This new technique entails removing
excess quantities of algae which, if left to proliferate, cause
ecological imbalances in the sea. Acid and chlorine free.''
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand, disappointed materialists are wallowing in
this week's sad developments: MSNBC reports that the  &UR; Jesse &LR; 
 &UR; Ventura &LR;  action figure, once available on the Minnesota governor's
Web site, is no longer available (the governor's office isn't
saying why). And the Victoria and Albert Museum, which is showing a
dress worn by  &UR; Sophie Rhys-Jones &LR; , has turned down the opportunity
to display the dress  &UR; Princess Diana &LR;  wore when she danced with
 &UR; John Travolta &LR; .  &UR; Catherine Walker &LR; , designer of that frock, told
the Mirror that the turn-down was ``an enormous blow.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPECIAL DEEDS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A delicious little San Francisco secret: Some mysterious good
soul has set up the  &UR; Martha Stewart &LR;  Foundation for Important
Superficial Projects, which provides money for small acts of civic
improvement. Grants are given without application; recipients keep
mum.
</P>
<P>
   Furthermore,  &UR; Nate Thornton &LR;  of Hayward, who is 85 years old, is
off this weekend to Fort Benning, Ga., where he'll be part of an
estimated contingent of 10,000 people protesting the U.S. military
training foreign soldiers on U.S. soil at taxpayers' expense. To
Thornton, it's one in a lifetime of demonstrations that began when
he went off (with his father) to fight in the Spanish Civil War, at
the age of 21.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GIFT IDEA NO. 6 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Never mind the angst of hiring a ghostwriter, the boredom of
listening to yourself drone into a tape recorder. If you feel your
friends and relatives are missing something by not knowing every
little detail about you, if you want to write an autobiography the
E-Z way, you might try ``the popular and respected 128-page
guidebook/workbook, `This Is My Life _ My Autobiography,' ''
suggested as a holiday gift by  &UR; Dyann &LR; 
 &UR; Espinosa &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All you do is open the $15.95 book or download the $9.95 text.
``Compose your life history with (an) easy-to-follow,
well-organized format. ... Helpful prompts and memory triggers
allow for thoughtful individualized responses.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Following the success of ``The Bone Collector,'' in which
 &UR; Denzel Washington &LR;  plays a paralyzed forensics expert, Filmland
News reports that New Line Cinema has signed &UR; Edward Norton &LR;  to play
the lead in ``Motherless Brooklyn.'' The movie, adapted from the
novel by  &UR; Jonathan Lethem &LR; , is about a detective who has Tourette's
syndrome.
</P>
<P>
   _ Glamour magazine asked Bloomingdale's fashion director  &UR; Kal &LR; 
 &UR; Ruttenstein &LR;  what he thought of a new purse designed by  &UR; Monica &LR; 
 &UR; Lewinsky &LR; . ``If I were Monica,'' he said, ``I'd put my label inside
the bag, not outside like it is. I realize she's a celebrity, but
nobody wants to wear their labels on the outside.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Edwin Heaven &LR;  ran into  &UR; Jerry Greenfield &LR;  of Ben &AMP; Jerry's at
Rose Pistola in San Francisco, and suggested a new ice cream
flavor: Coffee and Donuts, a portion of the profits from which
could be donated to the Police Athletic League. The problem would
be preventing the ice cream from making the doughnut too doughy;
the solution might be chocolate coating.
</P>
<P>
   _ The British newspaper the Sun reports that  &UR; Prince Charles &LR; 
and  &UR; Camilla Parker Bowles &LR;  are planning a bring-your-own-bottle
party for their neighbors on New Year's Eve, but Charles' office
called the report ``speculation entirely.''
</P>
