</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL-FILM (Hollywood) _ Digital technologies are beginning to
seep into Hollywood's mainstream. Mike Figgis, the British director
best known for the Oscar-winning ``Leaving Las Vegas,'' is at the
very least extraordinarily ambitious, some might say audacious,
about exploiting these digital technologies. By Rick Lyman. (The
story has moved in ``e'' news file.) 1,800 words.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
