for final combat training on the island of Vieques in case the
White House orders the change as part of a compromise to reopen the
Puerto Rican target range. The Navy says it is getting ready for
the unwanted change after encountering problems preparing the
destroyer USS John Hancock for duty in the Persian Gulf without
gunfire training on Vieques. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
