</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Hillary Rodham Clinton has
learned that silence is not always golden, a valuable lesson in
running for public office. Silence can generate as much criticism
as exaggerated rhetoric. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
