<SLUG> BC-BARGAINS21-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bargain dressing for the holidays
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Nov. 21
 &HT;    Alma E. Hill
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Who says dressing like a diva this holiday season has to be
expensive?
</P>
<P>
   You can have a snazzy new outfit for Thanksgiving, another for
your office Christmas party, plus something for all the dinner
parties, family gatherings and other holiday functions you plan to
attend. And you can have it all on a budget.
</P>
<P>
   It just takes a little coordination, an eye for fashion and a
knack for finding good buys.
</P>
<P>
   The key is selecting one outfit, preferably a suit, that can be
worn with several different tops or bottoms. We started with one
pantsuit, two blouses, a skirt and a handbag, and ended up with six
stylish outfits _ for less than $150.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
