<P>
   These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Business
section plans to move for Friday, November 19, on the New York
Times wire. For questions, please call Georgie Dennison at
415-777-6055 or the business desk at 415-536-5172. For business
stories running in main news, call the news desk at 415-777-7074.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FOR S.F. CHRONICLE PAGE 1 &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PUC &LR;  _ Pacific Bell can almost double the cost of calling 411
from a residential phone, state regulators voted yesterday. Despite
receiving 42,000 messages from citizens mostly opposed to the rate
hike, the state Public Utilities Commission allowed Pac Bell to
raise the charge for local directory assistance from 25 cents to 46
cents per call. The board voted down a compromise plan to allow a
charge of only 35 cents per call. By Benny Evangelista
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; FOR BUSINESS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; AFLCI0 _ &LR;  Look for the union ... portal? Yes, in these waning days
of the century, the AFL-CIO has discovered the Internet. Starting
December 1, members in the 68 affiliated unions can double click
their way to solidarity through a common portal _  &LR; 
 &LR; www.workingfamilies.com. Union leaders also plan to offer
computers to members for as little as $600, and cut-rate Internet
access. By Sam McManis
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Y2K  &LR; _ Banks have readied their computers for the year 2000 and
should cruise into the new year with few problems, a top federal
regulator said in San Francisco yesterday. By Sam Zuckerman
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; AGILENT _  &LR; Hewlett-Packard shareholders enjoyed a $13.6 billion
bonanza yesterday, thanks to an unexpectedly favorable earnings
report and the rousingly successful initial public offering of the
company's Agilent subsidiary. The Palo Alto computer-maker, with
more than 1 billion shares outstanding, soared $13.31 to $94.31 in
New York Stock Exchange trading _ its highest close in more than
seven weeks. By Arthur M. Louis
</P>
