<HEADLINE>
ABC'S QUIZ SHOW GETS ITS FIRST MILLIONAIRE 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOHN CARMAN  
 c.1999, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The ABC quiz show ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire'' has its
first millionaire, a network source said Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   The source said a contestant won the show's jackpot during a
program taped Thursday in New York and scheduled to air at 8:30
p.m. Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The source was unable to provide the identity of the contestant
but said it's a man who correctly identified the only U.S.
president to appear on the TV show ``Laugh-In.''
</P>
<P>
   One contestant ``lifeline'' provided by the show _ a phone call
to a relative _ was used by the player to help confirm the winning
answer, the source said.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest previous ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire'' winner
was a lawyer named Michael Shutterly, who won $500,000 in August.
</P>
<P>
