<HEADLINE>
TIMES NAMES EDITOR OF NEW SUPPLEMENT 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   William Norwich has joined The New York Times Magazine as editor
of a new supplement, ``Style and Entertaining,'' which will make
its debut Nov. 5, 2000. He will also edit Entertaining features for
the weekly magazine beginning Feb. 13.
</P>
<P>
   Norwich, who has contributed to Fashions of The Times, was
editor at large at Vogue magazine and an editor at Conde Nast House
&AMP; Garden. He wrote an around-the-town column for The Daily News in
New York until 1991, then wrote a column for The New York Post
until 1993.
</P>
<P>
   His Style Diary, a report on fashion, interior design and
manners, appears weekly in The New York Observer. His novel,
``Learning to Drive,'' was published by Grove/Atlantic in 1996. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
